        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The ground con­di­tion for a project may not be uni­form. It can change within short dis­tances in­side a tun­nel. Tun­nelling crew need to be pre­pared for that. Some of the ground con­di­tions that one may en­counter in­clude treated soft ma­rine clay on re­claimed land, and ground with boul­der and weath­ered rocks. There may also be ar­ti­fi­cial un­der­ground ob­struc­tions such as aban­doned for­mer South Wharf struc­tures and PUB deep sewer man­holes.</p>


